defaultWritten evidence submitted by the Grantham Research Institute on Climate Change and The Environment (LCI0017)default&#xa0;defaultThe Centre for Climate Change Economics and Policy (CCCEP)default was established in 2008 to advance public and private action on climate change through rigorous, innovative research. The Centre is hosted jointly by the University of Leeds and the London School of Economics and Political Science. It is funded by the UK 
defaultEconomic and Social Research Council and Munich Re. More information about the Centre for Climate Change Economics and Policy can be found at: http://www.cccep.ac.uk
